rently using harvard dataverse to share large datasets", "primary_storage": "Institutional cluster, Cloud storage, Community Archive (e.g., NDA, SRA, DANDI, DABI, BIL, NeMO, OpenNeuro, NEMAR, BossDB, etc.)", "data_sync_methods": ["Timestamping (embedding precise timestamps in data streams to align them temporally)", "Trigger Signals (using hardware or software triggers to mark events simultaneously across data streams)", "Hardware Synchronization (using dedicated hardware devices to synchronize data acquisition systems, such as TTL pulses or synchronization boxes)"], "behavioral_feature_detection": ["Statistical methods", "Computer vision methods (e.g., pose estimation)", "Domain-specific software - open source (e.g., BORIS, DeepLabCut)"], "feature_detection_software": ["dannce", "st3dio", "neuroposelib"], "analysis_languages": ["MATLAB", "Python"], "use_analysis_method": ["Classical statistical methods (e.g., t-tests, ANOVA)", "Computational models (e.g., Markov chains)", "Time series analysis", "Unsupervised machine learning (e.g., clustering, PCA)", "Supervised machine learning (e.g., classification, regression)", "Deep learning (e.g., neural networks, CNNs, RNNs)"], "use_analysis_types": ["Statistical analysis (e.g., t-tests, ANOVA)", "Signal processing (e.g., Fourier transforms, wavelet analysis, Dimensionality reduction (e.g., PCA, tSNE, UMAP), Dynamical systems modeling (e.g., state-space modeling, casual inference), Time-frequency analysis (e.g., spectrograms, coherence analysis), Bayesian inference, Encoding models, Decoding models, Correlation analysis, Regression models"], "analysis_software": ["Numpy", "Scipy (Python)", "Pytorch (Python)"], "analysis_platforms": ["Jupyter Notebook", "Command line terminal", "High-performance computing (HPC) systems", "Package managers and environments (e.g., Conda, Pip)", "Containerized environments (e.g., Docker)"], "reliability_methods": ["Cross-validation or resampling techniques (e.g., k-fold, bootstrapping)", "Sensi